Update on CCHF in Southern Russia (Stavropol & Dagestan & Kalmykia)
-------------------------------------------------------------------
According to data for Thu 10 May 2001, 6 cases of Crimean-Congo
hemorrhagic fever (CCHF) have been recorded in the Russian Federation: 2
cases in the Stavropol area (one patient died), 3 cases in the Republic of
Dagestan, and 1 case in the Republic of Kalmykia. On the basis of
provisional diagnosis (tick bites and clinical data) 15 people have been
hospitalized: 7 people in the Stavropol area and 8 in Dagestan (5 being
children younger than 14 years of age).
Specialists from the Viral Center of the Defence Ministry of Russia have
been sent to the Stavropol area, and the chief of a division of the
Department of the State Sanitary and Epidemiological Surveillance Service
of the Ministry of Health of Russia has been sent to the Republic of
Dagestan in order to provide practical help and coordinate activity.
